# Summary Statistics 
summary_stats <- Mortgage %>%
select(Loan.Amount, Estimated.Value, Qualification.FICO, Income.Type) %>%
summarise(
Mean_Loan_Amount = mean(Loan.Amount),
Median_Estimated_Value = median(Estimated.Value),
Mean_FICO = mean(Qualification.FICO),
Most_Common_Income_Type = names(which.max(table(Income.Type)))
  )

# Visualization with ggplot2
# histograms for Loan.Amount and Estimated.Value
loan_value_histogram <- Mortgage %>%
ggplot(aes(x = Loan.Amount)) +
geom_histogram(binwidth = 5000, fill = "blue", color = "black") +
labs(title = "Loan Amount Distribution")
print(loan_value_histogram)

value_histogram <- Mortgage %>%
ggplot(aes(x = Estimated.Value)) +
geom_histogram(binwidth = 5000, fill = "green", color = "black") +
labs(title = "Estimated Value Distribution")
print(value_histogram)

# a boxplot for Qualification.FICO
fico_boxplot <- Mortgage %>%
ggplot(aes(y = Qualification.FICO)) +
geom_boxplot(fill = "purple") +
labs(title = "FICO Score Distribution")
print(fico_boxplot)

#  a barplot for Income.Type
income_barplot <- Mortgage %>%
count(Income.Type) %>%
ggplot(aes(x = Income.Type, y = n)) +
geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "orange") +
labs(title = "Income Type Frequencies") +
theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))
print(income_barplot)
